# Post-change checklist

After completing any substantive change, ALWAYS end your response by prompting the user for each applicable action below. Do not silently skip steps or assume the user will remember.

## When to prompt

| Change made | Required follow-up |
|---|---|
| Any code / config / doc edit | **Commit** — ask if they want to commit (or commit yourself if asked) |
| `addsite2.md` or `addsite2-recipes/*.md` edited | **Sync** — run `pnpm sync:addsite2` before committing so `.claude/commands/addsite2.md` stays identical |
| Commit on `main` (server/worker/config changes) | **Deploy** — run the deploy script per the `deploy.mdc` rule |
| DB schema / migration added | **Migrate on prod** — remind to run `prisma migrate deploy` on the server |

## Wording

Keep it short and direct. At the end of your reply, add a line like:

> Next steps: commit these changes? / run `pnpm sync:addsite2` then commit? / deploy to prod?

Always list only the steps that actually apply to what was just changed.

## Batch the git steps — ask once, not one by one

When more than one of **sync / commit / push** (and/or **deploy**) applies,
offer them **together in a single question** and let the user approve the
whole sequence at once. Do NOT ask about each step in a separate turn.

> Next steps: sync (`pnpm sync:addsite2`), commit, and push these changes — do all? (then deploy?)

If the user says yes, run the applicable steps in the correct order
(sync → commit → push → deploy) without stopping to re-confirm each one.
